The '''cost of operation''' is the [[business strategy]] implemented in many companies to gain a huge market. Cost of operation is the cost acquired in completing one operation. It may be a conversion of [[Factors of production|inputs]] into the [[Output (economics)|outputs]] or [[labor costs]] etc. If the cost of operation is low then it is easy to maintain [[cost leadership]] and gain the [[Market (economics)|market]] with [[competitive advantage]].
