{{refimprove|biography|date=August 2014}}
'''Oloff Hennig''' is a South African businessman, best known for his friendship with [[Ronnie Biggs]], the legendary British train robber. He was also embroiled in a [[tax]] and murder scandal following the death of his [[accountant]].
Oloff is also reputed to have paved the way for South Africa’s rugby legend [[Naas Botha]]’s try-out as goal kicker for the [[Dallas Cowboys]].<ref>http://www.citypress.co.za/business/tokyos-guinea-deal-stirs-a-storm-20120623/</ref>
==Tax investigation== Hennig was embroiled in a tax and murder scandal when his accountant Marius van der Westhuizen was convicted of [[fraud]]. Van der Westhuizen was charged with filing false [[tax return]]s and fictitious figures on behalf of Oloff Hennig’s companies.<ref>[http://m.news24.com/dieburger/Suid-Afrika/Nuus/Man-beken-skuldaan-belastingbedrog-20110627 Jan Gerber, "Man beken skuld aan belastingbedrog"], ''News 24'' (28 June 2011)</ref>
Van der Westhuizen subsequently committed suicide before a sentencing for his crimes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/npa-praises-r1m-bail-forfeited-to-state-1505278|title=NPA praises R1m bail forfeited to State {{!}} IOL News|access-date=2018-06-29|language=en}}</ref>
==Links to Ronnie Biggs== Oloff Hennig was also a close friend of legendary British train robber [[Ronnie Biggs]]. Oloff visited him many times whilst Biggs lived in exile in [[Rio de Janeiro]]. Oloff even arranged for South African tourists to meet Biggs in Rio, where he would tell them how his gang conducted the [[Great Train Robbery (1963)]], during which they stole £2.6 million.<ref>[http://m.news24.com/citypress/Business/News/Tokyos-Guinea-deal-stirs-a-storm-20120623 Jacques Dommisse, "Tokyo’s Guinea deal stirs a storm"], ''City Press'' (24 June 2012)</ref>
==Personal life== Oloff is the father of [[Walter Hennig]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Joubert|first1=Pearlie|title=Who is Walter Hennig?|url=https://www.pressreader.com/south-africa/sunday-times/20140629/281685432936586|website=pressreader|publisher=Newspaperdirect Inc|accessdate=19 February 2017}}</ref>
